      "review_summary": "The PR changes CLI post-turn transcript compaction failure handling so native-harness and context-engine failures warn and continue instead of propagating as turn-level errors.\n\nPR surface: Source +23. Total +23 across 2 files.\n\nReproducibility: yes. source-level: current main persists the CLI transcript, awaits post-turn compaction before final delivery, and throws on terminal native/context compaction failure. I did not run a live forced Codex app-server failure in this read-only review.",
